} To implement DI, we need two things: We need a way to register a global Database at runtime to a particular instance, e.g. MySQL or Postgres. We need a way to describe a constructor for WebServer that fetches the registered Database instance. With these pieces, we can use our DI system like so: let mut manager = DIManager::new();
manager.build::<MySQL>().unwrap();
